		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.sourcememory.net/veleda/?p=126#comment-449</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[All people have this potential. Sadly we know much less than we could have about Bernedette&#039;s visions because of Church interference (they locked her away in a convent where she was not allowed to speak about her experiences to her peers, only to high clergy and high society visitors who kept asking all the wrong questions, over and over. (Color of the Lady&#039;s shoes, and other details that missed the essence of her experience.) Her very low social position as a poor woman gave her few alternatives, but you have to wonder what she would have manifested if she had become the guardian priestess of the Lourdes grotto, as her ancient ancestors might have done. In any case, her vision and devotion was to the Female Divine, as with so many other mystics including Ramakrishna.]]></description>
		<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p>All people have this potential. Sadly we know much less than we could have about Bernedette&#8217;s visions because of Church interference (they locked her away in a convent where she was not allowed to speak about her experiences to her peers, only to high clergy and high society visitors who kept asking all the wrong questions, over and over. (Color of the Lady&#8217;s shoes, and other details that missed the essence of her experience.) Her very low social position as a poor woman gave her few alternatives, but you have to wonder what she would have manifested if she had become the guardian priestess of the Lourdes grotto, as her ancient ancestors might have done. In any case, her vision and devotion was to the Female Divine, as with so many other mystics including Ramakrishna.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
